\par \pard\plain \widctlpar \f5\fs18 Because test mode (F7) bypasses the disk, not dropping frames in Testing mode usually means your disk I/O system is not keeping up with the capture operation.  If you are using AVICap mode, try switching to
\par Internal mode.  If you are using Internal mode, check the Disk I/O settings.  Consider increasing the number of cache chunks to 4 and changing the cache chunk size.
\par \pard \widctlpar 
